This is a simple char diver using dynamic allocation with "alloc_chrdev_region"

Please make sure to define your major and minor numbers first, and make sure they match the ones you will use as parameters in the make

To run use:

$ make major=your_major_number minor=your_major_number

after that just follow the instructions on the screen and each time you want to access the driver use

$ ./test

To remove the driver use

$ make clean
